\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {A.14}{\ignorespaces Nutrient factor evolution under the baseline scenario. The water nutrient factor $\nu _w$ declines due to cumulative drought stress, while fertilizer, temperature, and radiation factors remain closer to 1.0 (no stress). The declining $\nu _w$ (which later recovers) reduces effective growth rates and carrying capacities throughout the season.}}{44}{figure.14}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:nutrient-factors}{{A.14}{44}{Nutrient factor evolution under the baseline scenario. The water nutrient factor $\nu _w$ declines due to cumulative drought stress, while fertilizer, temperature, and radiation factors remain closer to 1.0 (no stress). The declining $\nu _w$ (which later recovers) reduces effective growth rates and carrying capacities throughout the season}{figure.14}{}}
